'''搜尋建議下拉式選單'''是使用電腦在搜尋時的一種功能，當使用者將欲搜尋的字詞輸入到搜尋框內後，在搜尋完成之前，會在搜尋框下方顯示下拉式選單，提出可供使用者點選的建議搜尋字詞，讓使用者可以快速完成搜尋。這種功能是[[自動完成|自動完成]]的一種形式，此列表與搜尋歷史記錄不同，即使使用者第一次搜尋，也會出現此建議選單。這些建議可能根據熱門搜尋、贊助商、使用者的地理位置或其他原因而有不同<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thingsontop.com/googles-new-search-suggestions-may-kill-your-website-158.html|title=Google's new search suggestions may kill your website|first=Vegard|last=Sandvoid|publisher=Things On Top|date=2008-12-14|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2018-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829151451/http://www.thingsontop.com/googles-new-search-suggestions-may-kill-your-website-158.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://diegobasch.com/search-for-obama-on-facebook-and-you-get-romney|title=Search for Obama on Facebook and you get Romney|first=Diego|last=Basch|date=2012-09-19|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112015453/https://diegobasch.com/search-for-obama-on-facebook-and-you-get-romney|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="se-land">{{cite web|url=http://searchengineland.com/how-google-instant-autocomplete-suggestions-work-62592|title=How Google Instant's autocomplete suggestions work|first=Danny|last=Sullivan|publisher=Search Engine Land|date=2011-04-06|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2020-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120021206/https://searchengineland.com/how-google-instant-autocomplete-suggestions-work-62592|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。在作業系統、網頁瀏覽器、搜尋引擎和各類網站中，這種功能很常見，在2014年的一項調查中指出，有80%以上的電子商務網站都有這項功能。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2014/08/the-current-state-of-e-commerce-search/|title=The current state of e-commerce search|first=Christian|last=Holt|publisher=Smash Magazine|date=2014-08-18|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2021-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211020557/https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2014/08/the-current-state-of-e-commerce-search/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

雖然Google不是這個功能的創始者，但作為全球市佔率最高的Google搜尋功能，其搜尋建議非常知名。這項功能由Google工程師Kevin Gibbs在2004年開發，由[[梅麗莎·梅爾|梅麗莎·梅爾]]定名<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allthingsd.com/20130823/nearly-a-decade-later-the-autocomplete-origin-story-kevin-gibbs-and-google-suggest/|title=Nearly a Decade Later, the Autocomplete Origin Story: Kevin Gibbs and Google Suggest|first=Liz|last=Gannes|publisher=All Things D|date=2013-08-23|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2021-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117065720/http://allthingsd.com/20130823/nearly-a-decade-later-the-autocomplete-origin-story-kevin-gibbs-and-google-suggest/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。包括Google在內，許多提供搜尋引擎功能的大型企業都設有搜尋建議黑名單，以防搜尋建議中出現某些違反其企業社會責任的建議。儘管如此，這些企業仍然會不時收到投訴，要求將一些被認為不恰當的建議內容或因[[網路機器人|網路機器人]]而大幅增加搜尋次數的建議內容添加到黑名單之中<ref name="se-land" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://utopiaordystopia.com/2015/02/22/truth-and-prediction-in-the-dataclysm/|title=Truth and Prediction in the Dataclysm|first=Rick|last=Searle|publisher=Utopia or Dystopia|date=2015-02-22|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2021-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120024721/https://utopiaordystopia.com/2015/02/22/truth-and-prediction-in-the-dataclysm/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[電子前哨基金會|電子前哨基金會]]的{{link-en|吉利安·約克|Jillian York}}批評了蘋果電腦的黑名單，指出其中有些詞彙僅因為具挑釁性質就入列。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/07/16/the-apple-kill-list-what-your-iphone-doesn-t-want-you-to-type.html|title=The Apple 'Kill List': What your iPhone doesn't want you to type|first=Michael|last=Keller|publisher=The Daily Beast|date=2013-07-16|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2017-05-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531135026/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/07/16/the-apple-kill-list-what-your-iphone-doesn-t-want-you-to-type.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在[[聯合國婦女署|聯合國婦女署]]於2013年發布的「自動完成的真相」系列廣告中，顯示出社會對女性的刻板印象被反映在搜尋建議之中。在廣告中，搜尋框內輸入了「women should」（女人應該），下方的建議顯示「女人應該持家」、「女人應該當奴隸」、「女人應該掌廚」等語句<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adweek.com/adfreak/after-viral-success-inequality-ads-creators-say-they-will-expand-campaign-153363|title=After viral success of inequality ads, creators say they will expand campaign|first=David|last=Griner|publisher=Ad Week|date=2013-10-24|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2018-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181223090457/https://www.adweek.com/adfreak/after-viral-success-inequality-ads-creators-say-they-will-expand-campaign-153363/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而在一則《{{link-en|壞天文學|Bad Astronomy}}》的故事中，搜尋建議顯示出對科學家不信任的觀點<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/bad_astronomy/2013/12/04/search_engine_bias_scientists_are.html|title="Scientists are..."|first=Phil|last=Plait|publisher=Slate|date=2013-12-04|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2018-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617093717/http://www.slate.com/blogs/bad_astronomy/2013/12/04/search_engine_bias_scientists_are.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。搜尋建議也可能會讓某些姓名與罪名並列，進而造成負面影響。<ref name="japan">{{cite web|url=http://www.tamingthebeast.net/blog/online-world/google-autocomplete-angst.htm|title=Some Folks *Really* Hate Autocomplete|first=Michael|last=Bloch|publisher=Taming The Beast|date=2012-03-27|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2020-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126235629/http://www.tamingthebeast.net/blog/online-world/google-autocomplete-angst.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://ijlit.oxfordjournals.org/content/23/3/261.full|title=Search engine liability for autocomplete suggestions: personality, privacy and the power of the algorithm|first1=Stavroula|last1=Karapapa|first2=Maurizio|last2=Borghi|journal=International Journal of Law and Information Technology|volume=23|pages=261–289|year=2015|accessdate=2016-08-03|archive-date=2016-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161205051748/http://ijlit.oxfordjournals.org/content/23/3/261.full|dead-url=no}}</ref>

